## TypeScript Types (Mobile / Clients)

### SearchResponse (evolved)

```typescript
export interface SearchResponse {
  exact_match: MCBaseItem | null;  // NEW
  tv: MCBaseItem[];
  movie: MCBaseItem[];
  person: MCBaseItem[];
  podcast: MCBaseItem[];
  author: MCBaseItem[];
  book: MCBaseItem[];
  news: MCBaseItem[];
  video: MCBaseItem[];
  ratings: MCBaseItem[];
  artist: MCBaseItem[];
  album: MCBaseItem[];
}
```

### Stream event handlers

```typescript
// Result event - unchanged shape
es.addEventListener("result", (e) => {
  const data: { source: SearchSource; results: MCBaseItem[]; latency_ms: number } = JSON.parse(e.data);
  // ...
});

// NEW: exact_match event
es.addEventListener("exact_match", (e) => {
  const item: MCBaseItem = JSON.parse(e.data);
  // Surface immediately - likely what user is looking for
});

es.addEventListener("done", () => es.close());
```

---

## Backwards Compatibility

- **Non-stream:** Adding `exact_match` is additive; existing clients can ignore it
- **Stream:** New event type `exact_match`; clients that only listen for `result` and `done` are unchanged
